Package: SmoothPLS
Type: Package
Title: SmoothPLS algorithm for Categorical and Scalar Functional Data 
Version: 0.1.2
Date: 2026-04-08
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Francois", "Bassac",
      email = "fr.bassac@gmail.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: This package performs the Smooth PLS algorithm.
    It was developped during a PhD thesis between DECATHLON and INRIA 2022-2026.
    The Smooth PLS method does not decompose the data into a basis. Its 
    philosophy is that we know as precisely the data as we want and that for 
    every PLS component the weight functions are decomposed into the basis.
    For both one-state, multi-states Categorical Functional Data (CFD) and 
    Scalar Functional Data, the smooth PLS algorithm is implemented for a 
    scalar response.
    In order to have a naive baseline, naive PLS method on value function of 
    time is also implemented.
